.SH "NAME"
megafs \- Mount remote filesystem locally via FUSE
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.nf
\fImegafs\fR [\-o <options>\&...] [\-d] [\-f] <mountpoint>
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
Mounts remote filesystem locally via FUSE\&.
.sp
\fBNOTE\fR: Be aware that reading and writing files is not implemented yet\&. You can only manage directories and remove files\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
\-o <options>
.RS 4
Additional mount options\&.
.sp
Some useful options may be: kernel_cache, auto_cache, allow_other, allow_root, nonempty\&.
.RE
.PP
\-d
.RS 4
Run filesystem in debug mode\&.
.RE
.PP
\-f
.RS 4
Run filesystem in foreground mode\&.
.RE
.PP
\-u <email>, \-\-username <email>
.RS 4
Account username (email)
.RE
.PP
\-p <password>, \-\-password <password>
.RS 4
Account password
.RE
.PP
\-\-config <path>
.RS 4
Load configuration from a file
.RE
.PP
\-\-ignore\-config\-file
.RS 4
Disable loading \&.megarc
.RE
.PP
\-\-no\-ask\-password
.RS 4
Never ask interactively for a password
.RE
.PP
\-\-disable\-previews
.RS 4
Never generate and upload file previews, when uploading new files
.RE
.PP
\-\-reload
.RS 4
Reload filesystem cache
.RE
.PP
\-\-debug [<options>]
.RS 4
Enable debugging of various aspects of the megatools operation\&. You may enable multiple debugging options separated by commas\&. (eg\&.
